'She was an intelligent, bubbly, popular girl who was much-loved by everyone in her family and all her friends.

'She had enjoyed her time at Abraham Guest High School and Saint John Rigby College and had just started at Liverpool Hope University.

'Alisha was studying Marketing and Media which she hoped would lead to a career in that field.

'No-one can ever expect or prepare for losing a child at such a young age. It is every parent's worst nightmare and we are utterly devastated.

'We are proud to have spent the time with her, and are comforted by all the love and messages of support we have received from family, friends and neighbours.

'They show just what a beloved and treasured person Alisha was to so many people.'

